'''Martin Lundstedt''' (born 28 April 1967 in [[Mariestad]], Sweden) is a Swedish businessman and has been President and CEO of the [[Volvo Group]] since 22 October 2015.<ref name="Press release AB Volvo, Martin Lundstedt appointed President and CEO of the Volvo Group">[http://www.volvogroup.com/group/global/en-gb/newsmedia/pressreleases/_layouts/CWP.Internet.VolvoCom/NewsItem.aspx?News.ItemId=149907&News.Language=en-gb "Press release AB Volvo, Martin Lundstedt appointed President and CEO of the Volvo Group"] 2015-04-22</ref> He has 25 years' experience of development, production and sales within the heavy automotive industry.

Martin Lundstedt studied at [[Chalmers University of Technology]] and graduated with an MSc Following his exam, he joined [[Scania AB|Scania]] as a trainee in 1992 and held a number of senior management positions during his 23 years with the company. He became the President and CEO at [[Scania AB|Scania]] in 2012 and remained in that position until joining the [[Volvo Group]].

