{{Orphan|date=June 2013}} {{Infobox magazine | title = World Economic Journal | image_file = [[File:World Economic Journal covers.jpg|250px]] | editor = [[Robert Abdullin]] | editor_title = [[Editor-in-chief]] | category = [[Economics]] | language = English, French, German, Russian, Spanish | publisher = | frequency = Monthly | firstdate = 2009 | website = {{URL|http://world-economic.com}} | oclc = 846509543 | issn = 2219-6374 }} The '''''World Economic Journal''''' ({{lang-ru|Международный Экономический Журнал}}) is a monthly business [[magazine]] published in Russian and English. The international English edition covers world economic data, dynamics, and analytics directly from Russia.
==History== The magazine was established by the British not-for-profit partnership [[World Organization of Creditors]] in 2009 and is regularly published in Russia since then. It is published and distributed in the United States and Canada since 2011. Since 2013, three additional editions are available: French, German and Spanish.
==Distribution== In the United States, the magazine is sold through [[Hudson News]].<ref>[http://world-economic.com/spread.html Distribution of World Economic Journal]</ref> In Russia, it is distributed by subscription and presented at international economic forums, conferences, and relevant organizations and structures, such as the [[State Duma]], the [[Federation Council (Russia)|Federation Council of the Russian Federation]], the [[Chamber of Commerce and Industry of the Russian Federation]], the [[Ministry of Economic Development (Russia)|Ministry of Economic Development of the Russian Federation]], the [[:ru:Ассоциация российских банков|Association of Russian banks]] and others.
